From: pasta-paul <paul@sunday.market>
Date: 2026-05-26
Subject: [PATCH] [DSv4][Quant] wo_a scale getattr fallback for non-MarlinFP8 paths

vllm/models/deepseek_v4/nvidia/ops/attention.py:377 reads
`self.wo_a.weight_scale_inv` directly. This attribute is only created
by MarlinFP8ScaledMMLinearKernel.process_weights_after_loading, which
renames `weight_scale` → `weight_scale_inv` for block-quantized FP8
layers (compressed_tensors_w8a16_fp8.py:120-130).

When the dispatcher selects a non-Marlin kernel for `wo_a` (e.g. when
the layer is correctly routed to TritonFp8BlockScaledMMKernel by the
preceding MarlinFP8.can_implement guard), the rename does not happen
and the attribute is missing. `self.wo_a.weight_scale` still exists —
the artifact ships scales under that name (llmcompressor.model_free_ptq
output convention).

Fix: getattr fallback. Math-equivalent to either path. Keeps the
canonical `weight_scale_inv` lookup as the primary read.

Verified on canada-quant/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-NVFP4-FP8-MTP, RTX PRO 6000
Blackwell. Without this patch: AttributeError at attention.py:377.
With this patch: engine init completes, profile_run succeeds, model
serves real completions.

Signed-off-by: pasta-paul <paul@sunday.market>
---
 vllm/models/deepseek_v4/nvidia/ops/attention.py | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/vllm/models/deepseek_v4/nvidia/ops/attention.py b/vllm/models/deepseek_v4/nvidia/ops/attention.py
--- a/vllm/models/deepseek_v4/nvidia/ops/attention.py
+++ b/vllm/models/deepseek_v4/nvidia/ops/attention.py
@@ -374,7 +374,9 @@ class _DeepseekV4SparseMLAAttentionImpl(...):
         )

         wo_a_fp8 = self.wo_a.weight
-        wo_a_scale = self.wo_a.weight_scale_inv
+        # Some quant kernels (Triton block-FP8 path) don't rename `weight_scale`
+        # → `weight_scale_inv`. Accept either; math is identical.
+        wo_a_scale = getattr(self.wo_a, "weight_scale_inv", None) or self.wo_a.weight_scale

         z = _allocate_deepseek_v4_wo_a_output(
             num_tokens,
